-# Explicitly load the applab i18n strings here, so we can organize the
-# relevant strings on this page into the applab bucket.
%script{src: webpack_asset_path("js/#{js_locale}/applab_locale.js")}
%script{src: webpack_asset_path('js/maker/setup.js')}

:css
  .main {
    width: 80%;
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .board-descriptions {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
  }

  .circuit-playground-description,
  .microbit-description {
    width: 45%
  }

  .maker-setup img {
    float: right;
    margin: 0 0 15px 10px;
  }

  .maker-setup .circuit-playground-description img,
  .maker-setup .circuit-playground img {
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  .validation-children div > p {
    font-size: 14px;
  }

-# If in the micro:bit experiment, display both the CP and MB board descriptions
- if request.params['enableExperiments'] === 'microbit'
  .maker-setup
    :markdown
      # CS Discoveries Maker Toolkit IT Setup
    .board-descriptions
      .circuit-playground-description
        :markdown
          ## The Circuit Playground

          <center><a href="https://learn.adafruit.com/introducing-circuit-playground/overview"><img src="#{image_url('maker/circuit-playground-200.jpg')}" width=200></a></center>

          The Adafruit [Circuit Playground Express](https://www.adafruit.com/product/3399) (and the older [Circuit Playground Classic](https://www.adafruit.com/product/3000)) is a programmable circuit board with built-in components that make getting started with physical computing quick and fun.

          In unit 6 of [Computer Science Discoveries](https://code.org/educate/csd) students use the Circuit Playground tethered via USB to their computers to allow for online curriculum integration and interactive debugging of programs.

          Please follow the instructions below to connect your board to Code.org.
      .microbit-description
        :markdown
          ## The micro:bit

          <center><a href="https://microbit.org/"><img src="#{image_url('maker/microbit-drawing-green.png')}" width=200></a></center>

          The [micro:bit](https://microbit.org/) is a circuit board designed by the BBC with a variety of sensors and other components, like a compass and an 8 by 8 array of programmable LEDs.

          Please follow the instructions below to connect your board to Code.org.
    :markdown
      <div id="setup-status-mount"/>
- else
  .maker-setup
    .circuit-playground
      :markdown
